description._content:
SS EURIMBLA was a steel screw steamship built by J Key and Sons in Kinghorn, Scotland in 1884. It was owned by the Australasian United Steam Navigation Company Ltd until 1905, when it was renamed HIDE MARU and owned and operated by S Koida, Japan. On 27 April 1907 it ran aground and was wrecked at Suyon Bay in Korea.

This photograph is part of the Australian National Maritime Museum's collection.

ANMM Collection Transfer from the Australian War Memorial.

The ANMM undertakes research and accepts public comments that enhance the information we hold about images in our collection. This record has been updated accordingly. 

Object no. ANMS0599[537]
